column1: Project Euler, Problem 280:  Ant and Seeds

column8: Sides of the gird have 'walls' - the ant cannot move outside
Ant can only move to adjacent square - no diagonal moves
Ant can carry only one seed at a time.
Ant may move to cell containing a seed, but can only drop seed in an empty cell, row 0
Ant may move to a cell containing a seed, but can carry only one seed at a time.
